{
  "stem": "9987.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Anyway, times were getting worse and worse and worse, until came 1941.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 1941, I think it was June 1st, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] or June 22nd, I think.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Germany attacked the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Germany attacked the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were under the impression that the Soviet Union is so strong.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were hopeful that finally going to come an end to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Germany was so strong, and so well organized [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that it took no time and the German army was in front of Leningrad, in front of Moscow, within I think a month or two, in the same year.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Hitler established a fuhrerhauptquartiere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That means the-- the headquarters for the general command, approximately 15 kilometers from our town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the headquarters for the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because this was closed to--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--the former border.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And since we had an airport in our town, one day, 1941 sometimes-- July, August, I don't remember-- I see a lot of things going on in town.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Small town, you can see so much police and Gestapo and soldiers, lining up the streets, on the roofs, all over to the main street.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Me being the way I was, like they say in-- like they said in-- in the Polish or Yiddish, [NON-ENGLISH], a risk-taker, I wanted to see what is going to-- what's happening in here.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And me with the armband on my-- on my-- on my coat, I get out to the marketplace to the main street among all these soldiers and police, and I'm standing and waiting, what's going to happen in here?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What's going on?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All of a sudden I hear from far away starting yelling, heil Hitler!",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Heil!",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Heil!",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
